Kyra B is more than a pretty face. She is hardworking, driven, focused, and letting nothing stand in her way. Kyra is a brand within a brand. She has successfully built a few brands while self-managing her model / acting career. Kyra has been featured in several major music videos and magazines, such as Jacquees "Bed" Yella Beezy "That's on me" remix and Sheen magazine that was in stores worldwide. Kyra is making her presence known throughout the acting industry. She has worked on several independent films and Tv shows. Kyra B made her debut on the tv show "For My Man' on Tv One Network.  Kyra B is not only an actress, music video/published model. She is a pose coach and creative director for numerous of models and artists photo shoots. Her creativity is one of a kind. She likes to say "I don't miss".  Kyra B is the leader of #themodelcitizenspot using her platform being a model advisor/coach teaching the skills you need to become a successful working model. She inspires upcoming models with one of her favorite quotes such as ''Global Not Local".

Kyra B is set to launch TheBluePrintByKyraB in the spring of 2023. She stated the mission for her new brand “ I am here to give you the blueprint of what I call fashion”.

- Networking is the process of making connections and building relationships. These connections can provide you with advice and contacts, which can help you make informed career decisions. Networking can even help you ﬁnd unadvertised jobs/internships.

- Networking is the exchange of information and ideas among people with a common profession or special interest, usually in an informal social setting. Networking often begins with a single point of common ground.

Tips to Help You Network Better !!

1. Meet People Through Other People
2. Leverage Social Media
3. Don’t Ask For A Job
4. Use Your Resume as a Tool for Advice
5. Don’t Take Up Too Much Time
6. Let The Other Person Speak
7. Present A Success Story 
8. Ask For Suggestions on How to Expand Your Network

Notes To Myself: Love Yourself 

1. “You matter. Your story matters. Your hopes, dreams and fears matter. All that you are matters.” 
2. “Fall in love with the process of becoming the best version of yourself.” 
3. “Self-love doesn’t come from fixing yourself; it comes from falling in love with parts of yourself you’ve been trying to fix.” 
4. “Let someone with a deep love to give, give that deep love to you, and what magic you’ll see.” – 
5. “Self- compassion is giving the same kindness to yourself that you would give to others.” 
6. “The real glow up is when you stop waiting to turn into some perfect version of yourself and consciously enjoy being who you are in the present.” 
7. “Love yourself first and everything else falls into line. You really have to love yourself to get anything done in this world.” 
8. “When you discover your self –worth you lose interest in anyone who doesn’t see it.” 
9. “You will not heal by tripping on the past. You only heal by accepting the present moment.” 
10. “Keep hope close to your heart and move forward. Maybe the road you are searching for today is not here yet. Do not be worried by it. Believe that a new path is ahead and what you have overcome along the way will give you strength.”

Who is KYRA B?!

Kyra B is originally from Bolivar, Tennessee she grew up in Jackson, Tennessee. Kyra moved to Nashville, Tennessee in October 2007 and Graduated from Pearl Cohn High School in 2008. She went to Tennessee State University from 2008 to 2012 that is when she discovered her life had a bigger calling in the entertainment industry. Kyra B was determined to take over Nashville, Tennessee with her many talents. Later down the years she took her talents to Atlanta, Georgia, where she currently resides. Kyra B is more than a pretty face. She is hardworking, driven, focused, and letting nothing stand in her way. Kyra is a brand within a brand. She has successfully built a few brands while self-managing her acting career. Kyra is making her presence known throughout the acting industry. She has worked on several independent films and Tv shows. Kyra B made her debut on the tv show “For My Man’ on Tv One Network. She also starred in Yella Beezy Video “That’s on me Remix”. 

Kyra B is not only an actress. She is a pose coach and creative director for numerous of models and artists photo shoots. Her creativity is one of a kind. She likes to say “I don’t miss”.

Kyra B is the leader of #themodelcitizenspot using her platform being a model advisor/coach teaching the skills you need to become a successful working model/actor. She inspires upcoming models/actors with one of her favorite quotes such as ‘’Global Not Local”.

I want to give a special thank you to the Instructional Designer Ms. Lyndell Edmondson  at John Early Museum Magnet Middle School. She informed me that I inspired her with my story but little does she  know, she has been an inspiration to me, There is a quote of hers that I apply daily. “ YOU CAN ACHIEVE, IF YOU ONLY BELIEVE”. 

The month of February, A celebration of African-American History will be held at John Early Museum Magnet Middle school!  I encourage you all to come out February 7th 10am-12pm and support our students! The students have worked so hard and diligently on their museum exhibits. I “KYRA B.” Am honored to be a feature. 

Please join me at John Early FEBRUARY 16th I am excited to speak with to our students as well as tour this awesome museum and view these amazing exhibits!

I do not take this matter lightly!!! I strive to make a positive impact on our youth especially to show them that with hard work, dedication, and the right mindset anything is possible!! I have worked very very hard for a long time while remaining consistent and humble, now I’m reaping the fruits of my labor and manifestation of my dreams!  With that being said Always Follow your dreams, never let up and remember; 
“NO ONE CAN YOU THE WAY THAT YOU CAN YOU”. - KYRA B
